DESCRIPTION:Committee of Adjustment\nmeetings will be held in-person at Ci
 ty Hall Council Chambers\, 426 Brant St. and virtually via Zoom videoconfe
 rencing technology.\nRequests to delegate at a meeting can be made by subm
 itting a written request by email to the Secretary Treasurer of the Commit
 tee of Adjustment at committeeofadjustment@burlington.ca or by phoning 905
 -335-7777\, ext. 7629 by noon the business day before the meeting is to be
  held. You are encouraged to pre-register as a delegate as soon as possibl
 e to facilitate an orderly registration process.\nIt is recommended that v
 irtual delegates include their intended remarks\, which will be circulated
  to all members in advance\, as a backup to any disruptions in technology 
 issues that may occur.\nIf you do not wish to delegate\, but would like to
  submit correspondence\, please email your comments to committeeofadjustme
 nt@burlington.ca. Any notes and comments will be circulated to the applica
 nt\, staff and members in advance of the meeting and will forming part of 
 the public record.\nThe link will be active 30 minutes before the start ti
 me.\nApplications will be heard in the order that they appear on the agend
 a or otherwise stated by the Chair.\nZoom Details\nWhen: Apr 22\, 2026 1:0
 0 PM Eastern Time (US and Canada)\nTopic:  Hybrid CoA Meeting No 7_1:00 P
 M\nJoin from PC\, Mac\, iPad\, or Android:\nhttps://us06web.zoom.us/j/8567
 9520680\nPhone one-tap:\n+15873281099\,\,85679520680# Canada\n+16473744685
 \,\,85679520680# Canada\nJoin via audio:\n+1 587 328 1099 Canada\n+1 647 3
 74 4685 Canada\n+1 647 558 0588 Canada\n+1 778 907 2071 Canada\n+1 780 666
